[01:05.59]	Sir Gilbert Peck his chancellor; and John Car,
[01:09.10]	Confessor to him; with that devil-monk,
[01:12.14]	Hopkins, that made this mischief.
[01:14.76]Second Gentleman	That was he
[01:16.00]	That fed him with his prophecies?
[01:18.69]First Gentleman	The same.
[01:19.72]	All these accused him strongly; which he fain
[01:23.24]	Would have flung from him, but, indeed, he could not:
[01:27.10]	And so his peers, upon this evidence,
[01:30.00]	Have found him guilty of high treason. Much
[01:33.38]	He spoke, and learnedly, for life; but all
[01:36.55]	Was either pitied in him or forgotten.
