[01:52.90]	And something spoke in choler, ill, and hasty:
[01:56.35]	But he fell to himself again, and sweetly
[01:59.59]	In all the rest show'd a most noble patience.
[02:03.11]Second Gentleman	I do not think he fears death.
[02:05.59]First Gentleman	Sure, he does not:
[02:07.17]	He never was so womanish; the cause
[02:10.00]	He may a little grieve at.
[02:12.21]Second Gentleman	Certainly
